## Root Cause Analysis
- The constraint logic for boards query is defined in [BoardQueryConstraints.java](https://github.com/lithiumtech/lia/blob/7e4c39a2f64769ebd284adf82ab59f645221e015/dev/lia/components/restv2/src/main/java/lithium/api/graphql/schema/query/nodes/BoardQueryConstraints.java)
- By default, ancestorId set as is
```
public void setAncestorId(IDEqlInConstraint ancestorId) {
	this.ancestorId = ancestorId;
}
```
- Our input is `category:canaries` which syntax is enforce by [IDEqlInConstraint.java](https://github.com/lithiumtech/lia/blob/f316ed90fe07ffceb02b4f527aa63dc61b22875c/dev/lia/components/restv2/src/main/java/lithium/api/graphql/schema/query/base/IDEqlInConstraint.java). That input is parsed to object IDRef, which is {type:category, id: canaries} in this case.
- If relying on default ancestorId implementation, only "canaries" is forwarded to next steps, which is not expected
- A similar situation can be seen through [NodeQueryConstraints.java](https://github.com/lithiumtech/lia/blob/b119cc982b0663d5309dcc84353c94cc6b362254/dev/lia/components/restv2/src/main/java/lithium/api/graphql/schema/query/nodes/NodeQueryConstraints.java) which also require similar syntax, such as "board:board-id". And it set ancestorId by:
```
@Override
public void setAncestorId(IDEqlInConstraint ancestorId) {
	super.setAncestorId(ancestorId.includeType());
}
```

=> This must be an edge case for boards query and cause by lack of proper OOP inheritance.

